OL,3,CTV-related anniversaries for 28 JUN
OL,4,CPROGRAMMES
OL,5,
OL,6,CG1981FThe BBC announces a major
OL,7,Fshake-up of the presentation of its TV
OL,8,Fnews programmes. As well as a complete
OL,9,Foverhaul of studio sets and title
OL,10,Fsequences, Peter Woon, editor, TV News,
OL,11,Ftook the decision to have more
OL,12,Fjournalists reading the news. The main
OL,13,Fpresenter changes:
OL,14,
OL,15,F(a) former correspondents John Humphrys
OL,16,Fand John Simpson would present the Nine
OL,17,Fo'Clock News;
OL,18,F(b) Richard Baker to present the
OL,19,FEvening News;
OL,20,F(c) Richard Whitmore to present the new
OL,21,Flunchtime bulletin - News After Noon -
OL,22,Falongside Moira Stuart;
OL,23,Sppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBOn This DayCClean FeedFNat TV
